{#-
  New York § 600.21(f) — Broker Compensation Disclosure Letter.

  Source-of-truth dossier: docs/compliance/02_new_york.md, section
  "Broker compensation: REQUIRED disclosure in NY (§ 600.21(f))":

      "When a broker is involved, the provider must inform the
       recipient in writing how, and by whom, the broker is compensated
       for their role in the transaction."

  NYDFS Assessment of Public Comments quoted in the dossier:
      "This general provision does not specify a form of disclosure.
       Financers have the discretion to explain broking fees, in
       writing, so long as their disclosures are accurate."

  This letter travels alongside (NOT inside) the standardized § 600.6
  disclosure. AEGIS is the broker; the funder is the provider. AEGIS
  delivers the letter on behalf of the funder relationship. The
  rendered HTML is locked by a snapshot test in
  tests/compliance/test_broker_compensation_letter.py.

  Visual idiom mirrors ny_cfdl.html.j2 (same masthead, fonts, footer
  metadata) so a recipient sees the two artifacts as a single package.

  Required context variables:
    broker_name                              str
    broker_registration                      str | None  — license / registration
                                                          identifier; row omitted
                                                          when None
    funder_name                              str
    recipient_name                           str
    transaction_id                           str
    letter_date                              str   — ISO date (rendered_at)
    total_compensation                       str   — pre-formatted "$X,XXX.XX"
    compensation_paid_by_funder              str   — "$X,XXX.XX"
    compensation_paid_by_recipient           str   — "$X,XXX.XX"
    contingent_compensation_description      str   — descriptive text or
                                                     "None" when no contingent
                                                     component exists
-#}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<title>Broker Compensation Disclosure — New York (§ 600.21(f))</title>
<style>
  body { font-family: -apple-system, sans-serif; max-width: 760px; margin: 24px auto;
         color: #111; }
  h1   { font-size: 18px; }
  h2   { font-size: 14px; margin-top: 18px; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 12px 0; }
  th, td { border: 1px solid #555; padding: 8px 10px; vertical-align: top;
           font-size: 12px; }
  th    { background: #f0f0f0; text-align: left; }
  .col1 { width: 44%; font-weight: 600; }
  .col2 { width: 56%; }
  .statute { background: #f7f7f7; border-left: 3px solid #555;
             padding: 10px 12px; margin: 12px 0; font-size: 11px;
             font-family: "SFMono-Regular", Menlo, Consolas, monospace; }
  .footer { margin-top: 16px; font-size: 11px; color: #333; }
  .meta   { font-size: 10px; color: #666; margin-top: 6px; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>Broker Compensation Disclosure</h1>
<p class="meta">New York — 23 NYCRR § 600.21(f). Provider: {{ funder_name }}.
Transaction: {{ transaction_id }}. Date: {{ letter_date }}.</p>

<p>To: {{ recipient_name }}</p>

<p>This written disclosure accompanies the Commercial Financing Disclosure
issued under 23 NYCRR § 600.6. It informs you how, and by whom,
{{ broker_name }} (the &ldquo;broker&rdquo;) is compensated in connection with the
financing offered to you by {{ funder_name }} (the &ldquo;provider&rdquo;).</p>

<h2>Broker identification</h2>
<table>
<tbody>
<tr>
  <td class="col1">Broker name</td>
  <td class="col2">{{ broker_name }}</td>
</tr>
{%- if broker_registration %}
<tr>
  <td class="col1">Broker license / registration</td>
  <td class="col2">{{ broker_registration }}</td>
</tr>
{%- endif %}
<tr>
  <td class="col1">Provider (financer)</td>
  <td class="col2">{{ funder_name }}</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<h2>Broker compensation for this transaction</h2>
<table>
<tbody>
<tr>
  <td class="col1">Total compensation the broker receives in connection
      with this transaction</td>
  <td class="col2">{{ total_compensation }}</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td class="col1">Amount paid by the provider to the broker</td>
  <td class="col2">{{ compensation_paid_by_funder }}</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td class="col1">Amount paid by the recipient to the broker</td>
  <td class="col2">{{ compensation_paid_by_recipient }}</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td class="col1">Contingent or variable compensation</td>
  <td class="col2">{{ contingent_compensation_description }}</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<p>You may request a written copy of this disclosure from the provider at
any time. Brokerage fees treated as prepaid finance charges are also
reflected in the finance charge of the accompanying § 600.6 disclosure,
as required by 23 NYCRR § 600.17.</p>

<p class="statute">23 NYCRR § 600.21(f): &ldquo;When a broker is involved, the
provider must inform the recipient in writing how, and by whom, the
broker is compensated for their role in the transaction.&rdquo;</p>

<p class="footer">New York Applicable law requires this information to be
provided to you to help you make an informed decision.</p>

<p class="meta">Generated by AEGIS on {{ letter_date }}. Per 23 NYCRR
Part 600 (§ 600.21(f)).</p>
</body>
</html>
